ADDITIONAL TERMS — Code of Conduct compliance
================================================================

The use, distribution, modification, or sublicensing of this Software
is conditional upon adherence to the project's Code of Conduct, set
out in CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md in this repository.

In plain language:

- The MIT permissions above grant you the right to use, copy, modify,
  publish, distribute, and sublicense the Software, on the standard
  MIT terms.
- You are also expected to behave according to the Code of Conduct
  in any context that involves this Software, the project, its
  contributors, or the people named or referenced in the codebase.

Violations of the Code of Conduct — including but not limited to:
doxxing or harassing contributors or third parties named in the
codebase, removing the privacy-tier classifications without consent,
introducing real names of Tier-2 individuals, performative or
abusive conduct in issues / merge requests, or knowingly publishing
content that the Code of Conduct forbids — will be pursued by all
appropriate legal means available under German law (the maintainer's
jurisdiction, see Impressum) and the jurisdiction in which the
violation occurred.

This Additional Terms section does not narrow the MIT permissions
above for any lawful, conduct-respecting use. It applies only when
conduct itself crosses into legally actionable territory
(harassment, defamation, doxxing, unlawful processing of personal
data, etc.).

If you fork this Software and remove the Code of Conduct, you also
remove this Additional Terms clause — but you remain bound by the
laws of your own jurisdiction, which in most cases cover the same
behaviours independently.
